text: Barsine cuneonotata, the footman moth, is a moth of the subfamily Arctiinae. The species was first described by Francis Walker in 1855. It is found in China, Thailand, India, Sri Lanka, Sumatra, Borneo, Singapore and the Philippines, Barsine cuneonotata - Doi Su thep, Chiang Mai (5922997001).jpg| ==References== Category:Moths of Asia Category:Moths described in 1855
